        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1377657418,
        "creation_date": 1377657418,
        "body": "<p>You are attempting to cast a <code>Byte[]<\/code> to a <code>byte[]<\/code>.  You can't do that in Java.<\/p>\n\n<p>You have two choices:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Change whatever is providing the <code>Byte[]<\/code> that is in <code>obj<\/code> to create a <code>byte[]<\/code> instead.<\/p><\/li>\n<li><p>Convert the <code>Byte[]<\/code> to a <code>byte[]<\/code>.  For example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Byte[] tmp (Byte[]) obj;\nbyte[] a = new byte[obj.length];\nfor (int i = 0; i &lt; a.length; i++) {\n    a[i] = tmp[i];\n}\n<\/code><\/pre><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
        "answer_id": 18478529,
        "question_id": 18478421
    }],
